Description:
*Join a Team Where Your Expertise Shapes the Energy Industry's Future*


Are you a measurement professional who loves solving complex data challenges? Do you thrive in a role where accuracy, analysis, and operational impact come together? At SPL, we’re looking for a skilled **Senior Measurement Data Analyst** who wants to make meaningful contributions in one of the most critical sectors of energy operations. Based in **Houston, TX,** this role gives you the chance to apply your technical depth, mentor others, and influence data integrity across the organization.

**About the Role**


The **Senior Measurement Data Analyst** plays a pivotal role in ensuring the accuracy, integrity, and reliability of measurement data used throughout the organization. You will validate, analyze, and reconcile complex datasets, support continuous improvement initiatives, and act as a technical authority in measurement processes. With your expertise, you will help maintain compliance, optimize workflows, and elevate our measurement standards.


This position is ideal for someone who enjoys investigating discrepancies, improving systems, and collaborating with cross\-functional teams to ensure flawless measurement operations.

**What You’ll Do**

* Validate, reconcile, and analyze measurement data across multiple platforms to ensure accuracy and compliance;
* Troubleshoot discrepancies in FLOWCAL, SCADA, EFM, and related systems;
* Perform complex data analysis to identify trends, anomalies, and root causes;
* Support internal and external audits, providing technical documentation and investigative findings;
* Collaborate with IT, Operations, Field Measurement, and Engineering teams to improve data reliability;
* Develop, revise, and maintain SOPs, workflows, and reporting processes;
* Lead or support continuous improvement initiatives to enhance data accuracy and measurement efficiency;
* Provide mentorship, technical support, and problem\-solving guidance to junior analysts and team members;
* Serve as a subject\-matter expert in measurement calculations, data integrity, and system performance;
* Perform other duties as assigned.

**Why You’ll Love Working Here**

* Competitive salary \+ performance\-based incentives;
* Medical, dental, and vision insurance;
* Paid parental leave for both parents;
* Employee Assistance Program (EAP) for mental, financial, and family well\-being;
* 401(k) with company match;
* Paid time off \+ paid holidays;
* Professional development and career advancement opportunities;
* Exposure to critical measurement systems and high\-impact projects;
* A collaborative, supportive culture in the energy capital of the world — Houston, TX.

**Your Schedule and The Fine Print**

* Full\-time position following a standard Monday through Friday schedule;
* Ability to work outside of scheduled hours, including evenings or weekends, as required to meet operational or workload needs.


Requirements:
**What You Bring**

* Bachelor’s degree in Engineering, Measurement Science, Data Analytics, or a related technical field; or equivalent experience;
* 5\+ years of experience in measurement data analysis, preferably in oil \& gas or energy sectors;
* Proficiency with FLOWCAL (required), SCADA systems, and measurement data platforms;
* Strong analytical skills with the ability to interpret complex datasets and reconcile discrepancies;
* Knowledge of industry measurement standards, regulatory requirements, and applicable guidelines;
* Experience performing root\-cause investigations and implementing corrective actions.

**Our Commitment to Diversity and Inclusion**


At SPL, we believe that a diverse team is a strong team. We are proud to be an equal opportunity employer, committed to creating an inclusive environment where all employees can thrive. We make all employment decisions based on qualifications, merit, and business needs, without regard to race, color, religion, sex, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, or any other legally protected characteristic. We are also committed to providing reasonable accommodations to applicants and employees with disabilities or for sincerely held religious beliefs, in accordance with applicable laws. If you need assistance or an accommodation during the application process, please let us know.

**Visa Sponsorship**


At this time, SPL is not able to offer visa sponsorship for this position. We sincerely appreciate your interest and understanding, and we encourage you to explore other opportunities with us that may be a fit in the future.
